Network Setup
What it is
Host IP: 172.16.0.10/24 (Static)

Web UI: Accessed via port 8006

Network Mode: [e.g., NAT or Routed]

Why it is set up this way
Reliability: Using a Static IP ensures the server is always easy to find on the network.

Security: Using a private IP range (172.16.x.x) is safe to document publicly while keeping your home network isolated.

Standard Access: Using port 8006 is the standard, clean way to manage Proxmox.

Connectivity: This network mode allows for controlled communication between the virtual machines and the host.
